column2: Ryan- we took the boats out of the water on Sept 29- 2013. If you want we will do this for you next year. Let me know.
Weather has been cloudy and windy for the last two weeks
More green than usual--still good swimming.
Cloudy- had to wait for blue sky -- nice weather
Lake turned over two days ago
Water nice- good swimming and boating
Nice day- small clouds; for water color- greenish deeper in water
Had to do on Sunday the 21st instead of 18th--cool day
Beautiful day -- could not get reading on Aug 26 and 27th.  Cloudy
Cloudy and windy- rain off and on

column1: Last reading / have taken boats out of water.  Weather beautiful- water beautiful- too bad winter is coming.

column2: a lot of rain in past week
from last week until low we have had 5.5 inches of rain
lots of wind and clouds and rain
rain off and on- bad week
lots of rain 4.5 inches- 3 inches one night in 1.5 hours
weather somewhat better than first part of summer
beautiful weather- nicest of the summer
nice day- lots of clouds- had to work between them
clouds off and on- had to work between clouds again
1st day it was very beautiful- very few clouds
I guess fall is trying to get here.

We are taking all boats out of water. This has not been a very nice summer. Our lake is 26 feet deep- we never touched the bottom this year. I'm thinking that because of all the rain- the lake was never clear enough. It seemed that we were always wet. I never used the sprinkler on the lawn all summer. Our lake is up 1 foot- 4 inches over last year.
